241	\section{Implementation route via the Albanese functor}
242	
243	Because the full Picard-scheme representability theorem is not available in current Mathlib, the formal construction proceeds in two layers:
244	
245	\begin{enumerate}
246	  \item \textbf{Layer I --- direct definition.} The Jacobian of $C$ is defined uniformly as the underlying scheme of the Albanese witness provided by Theorem~\ref{thm:nonempty_jacobianWitness}, carrying the four properties of Theorems~\ref{thm:Jacobian_grpObj}--\ref{thm:Jacobian_geomIrred} (each obtained by projection from the witness). The genus-$0$ case is included: the witness's universal property in that case implicitly carries the rigidity content $\Hom(\mathbb P^1_k, A) = A(k)$.
247	
248	  \item \textbf{Layer II --- Abel--Jacobi compatibility.} Chapter~\ref{chap:AbelJacobi} introduces the Abel--Jacobi morphism $C \to \Jac(C)$ and shows that it is universal among morphisms from $C$ to abelian varieties.
249	\end{enumerate}
